Before, a couple of questions:

## document vs ownerDocument

Event subscription [happens on `document`](https://github.com/mui-org/material-ui/blob/86de5254767be6f76edf7ca4b868452b22557df8/packages/material-ui/src/ClickAwayListener/ClickAwayListener.js#L84), whereas the contain check [happens on ownerDocument](https://github.com/mui-org/material-ui/blob/86de5254767be6f76edf7ca4b868452b22557df8/packages/material-ui/src/ClickAwayListener/ClickAwayListener.js#L65).

I guess as no bugs were filed this works alright. But in more than a few DnD libraries out there subscription happens on `ownerDocument` (eg, to support iframe).

So why subscribe on `document` rather `ownerDocument`?

## Why function and not arrow function?

As in with:

```js
function mapEventPropToEvent(eventProp) {
  return eventProp.substring(2).toLowerCase();
}
```

Is there some convention in the code regarding when to use one or the other?

